PSEUDO_CODE_ATTEMPTS

//

- a function that returns the sum of two numbers

START

Given two integer variables.
	- Return the sum of the two variables.
	- Save the value in a new variable named sum2.

Print sum2.


//

- A function that takes an array of strings, and returns a string that is all those strings concatenated together

START

Given an array of strings.
Join (concatenate) the individual strings to form one string.
Make sure there are spaces in between the old string bits.
Print the newly concatenated string.


//
- A function that takes an array of integers, and returns a new array with every other element.

START

Given an array with integers (myArray).
Create an indexing variable.
Create a new array (mySecondArray).
Iterate over the array beginning with an index of 0, while the index is less than the length of the string, and increasing the index by two.
Return each of the indexed integers in the array to mySecondArray.
Print mySecondArray.

